 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 03 - Job Recommendation Engine\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook builds and evaluates the Job Recommendation Engine, which uses TF-IDF vectorization and cosine similarity to find the top N matching jobs for a given resume. It also includes a basic skill gap analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
    "import pickle\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add src to path\n",
    "sys.path.append(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))), 'src'))\n",
    "from config import CLEANED_JOB_DATA_PATH, JOB_VECTORIZER_PATH\n",
    "from data.preprocess import preprocess_job_data\n",
    "from features.text_features import create_tfidf_features, load_vectorizer\n",
    "from models.recommender import get_recommendations, skill_gap_analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ensure directories exist\n",
    "os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(JOB_VECTORIZER_PATH), exist_ok=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load Data\n",
    "\n",
    "We load the preprocessed job dataset. If not available, we run the preprocessing step."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if not os.path.exists(CLEANED_JOB_DATA_PATH):\n",
    "    print("Cleaned job data not found. Running preprocessing...")\n",
    "    job_df = preprocess_job_data()\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print("Loading cleaned job data...")\n",
    "    job_df = pd.read_csv(CLEANED_JOB_DATA_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "if job_df is not None:\n",
    "    print(f"Loaded {len(job_df)} cleaned jobs.")\n",
    "    print(job_df.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Feature Engineering (TF-IDF for Jobs)\n",
    "\n",
    "We create TF-IDF features for the job descriptions. This vectorizer will be used to transform both job descriptions and resume texts into a common vector space."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if job_df is not None:\n",
    "    # Ensure no NaN in cleaned_text\n",
    "    job_df[\"cleaned_text\"] = job_df[\"cleaned_text\"].fillna(\'\')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Create TF-IDF features for job descriptions and save the vectorizer\n",
    "    tfidf_matrix, job_vectorizer = create_tfidf_features(job_df[\"cleaned_text\"])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    with open(JOB_VECTORIZER_PATH, \"wb\") as f:\n",
    "        pickle.dump(job_vectorizer, f)\n",
    "    print(f\"Job TF-IDF vectorizer saved to {JOB_VECTORIZER_PATH}\")\n",
    "    print(\"Job TF-IDF matrix shape:\", tfidf_matrix.shape)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    tfidf_matrix = None\n",
    "    job_vectorizer = None"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Job Recommendation\n",
    "\n",
    "We simulate a resume upload and get job recommendations based on cosine similarity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if job_df is not None and tfidf_matrix is not None:\n",
    "    # Example resume text (for demonstration)\n",
    "    sample_resume_text = \"Experienced Python developer with skills in machine learning, data analysis, and web development. Looking for roles in AI or software engineering.\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"\nGetting job recommendations for a sample resume...\")\n",
    "    recommendations = get_recommendations(sample_resume_text, tfidf_matrix, job_vectorizer, job_df, top_n=10)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if not recommendations.empty:\n",
    "        print(\"\nTop 10 Job Recommendations:\")\n",
    "        for idx, row in recommendations.iterrows():\n",
    "            print(f\"- {row[\"title\"]} at {row[\"company\"]} (Match Score: {row[\"match_score\"]:.2f})\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Perform skill gap analysis for the top recommended job\n",
    "            found_skills, missing_skills = skill_gap_analysis(sample_resume_text, row[\"skills\"])\n",
    "            print(f\"  Skills in Resume: {\", \".join(found_skills)}\")\n",
    "            print(f\"  Missing Skills: {\", \".join(missing_skills)}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"No recommendations found.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "The job recommendation engine has been successfully demonstrated, providing ranked job listings and a basic skill gap analysis based on a sample resume. The TF-IDF vectorizer for job descriptions is saved for use in the Streamlit application."
   ]
  }
 ],
